      "seed": 1733594353,
      "version": 620,
      "versionNonce": 1688855972,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782960301034,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\nrequirement:\n1. Hybrid Profile Generation : \n    The system utilizes a seed database of known entities for deterministic lookups, \n    while leveraging multimodal LLM APIs to dynamically identify and generate stats for unlisted public figures.\n2. Vector Storage & Similarity Search : \n    The PostgreSQL database must utilize the pgvector extension to store 512-dimensional face embeddings, \n    enabling low-latency cosine similarity searches ($<=>$) to match scanned faces.\n\nnon-requirement:\n1. Low Latency :\nFacial embedding extraction and database vector matching ($<=>$) must complete within < 200ms to ensure a smooth, real-time scanning experience.\n2. High Availability :\nThe API server and database cache layer should achieve 99.9% uptime during simulated traffic spikes.\n3. Cost Efficiency :\nMaximize cache hit rate to ensure < 5% of recurrent face scans trigger expensive multimodal LLM API tokens.\n\nArchitecture Boundaries & Constraint:\n1. Production-Grade Bio-Privacy Compliance:\n    Does not implement strict biometrics encryption or GDPR deletion workflows, \n    as database profiles are strictly anonymized using vector tokens without storing PII (Personally Identifiable Information).\n2. Enterprise Cluster Scalability:\n    All data is transmitted securely over HTTPS. \n    Facial images are processed for real-time de-identification on our FastAPI cloud server. \n    Only the anonymized feature vectors are saved to the encrypted Supabase database, \n    and the original raw images are never stored.",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\nrequirement:\n1. Hybrid Profile Generation : \n    The system utilizes a seed database of known entities for deterministic lookups, \n    while leveraging multimodal LLM APIs to dynamically identify and generate stats for unlisted public figures.\n2. Vector Storage & Similarity Search : \n    The PostgreSQL database must utilize the pgvector extension to store 512-dimensional face embeddings, \n    enabling low-latency cosine similarity searches ($<=>$) to match scanned faces.\n\nnon-requirement:\n1. Low Latency :\nFacial embedding extraction and database vector matching ($<=>$) must complete within < 200ms to ensure a smooth, real-time scanning experience.\n2. High Availability :\nThe API server and database cache layer should achieve 99.9% uptime during simulated traffic spikes.\n3. Cost Efficiency :\nMaximize cache hit rate to ensure < 5% of recurrent face scans trigger expensive multimodal LLM API tokens.\n\nArchitecture Boundaries & Constraint:\n1. Production-Grade Bio-Privacy Compliance:\n    Does not implement strict biometrics encryption or GDPR deletion workflows, \n    as database profiles are strictly anonymized using vector tokens without storing PII (Personally Identifiable Information).\n2. Enterprise Cluster Scalability:\n    All data is transmitted securely over HTTPS. \n    Facial images are processed for real-time de-identification on our FastAPI cloud server. \n    Only the anonymized feature vectors are saved to the encrypted Supabase database, \n    and the original raw images are never stored.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ySrYQcoxL2bafsQVdcFoR",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 37.51605077448221,
      "y": 320.68344030437095,
      "width": 2179.99462890625,
      "height": 70,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
